    "body": "If you have spare resources, run a 3rd node, that will confirm which node is incorrect, and can be rebuilt... I have encountered setups with nodes of the same version and settings, but different DB sizes. Only upon deeper inspection (eg running an indexer to inspect block by block), one of the nodes had issues returning txns. I have also seen nodes that are fine from the indexer's perspective, but still have different sizes. All these cases could be due to bugs that are caused by unexpected flows. As part of my maintenance routine, I periodically take a node offline from a cluster and rebuilt.",
